Account setup ( before posting ) - 
Before starting, properly prepare your page:
   Name and username
   Bio
   Logo/profile picture
   5 highlight ideas and cover 
   Music suggestions for profile
Pinned posts:
   Introduction
   Contact info
   Niche-related posts (e.g., “Best music of 2026”)
Switch to professional account
Select correct category
Follow some pages in your niche
All these steps improve your page’s SEO and discoverability on Instagram.
👉 Prompts and detailed video explanations for setup are provided in other files—make sure to check them.


Account Warmup - 
After creating your account, warm it up before posting.
For the next 5 days (30 minutes daily):
   Search relevant keywords in your niche
   Follow related pages and creators
   Watch their content
   Like, comment, and even share posts
This helps the algorithm understand your niche and improves initial reach.


Platform requirements - 
On Whop:
You usually do not need to register every single page.
You just need to:
    Join the campaign
    Submit video analytics for each post


On Discord Servers:
Requirements can vary depending on the server and requirements.
Some servers require:
    Page registration
    Account verification
Others only require:
    Submitting video analytics for each clip
👉 Always confirm requirements with the support team before starting.
